com.hannesdorfmann.mosby.dagger1

Interface Injector

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Dagger1MosbyActivity, Dagger1MosbyFragment, Dagger1MvpActivity, Dagger1MvpFragment, Dagger1MvpLceActivity, Dagger1MvpLceFragment, Dagger1MvpLceViewStateActivity, Dagger1MvpLceViewStateFragment, Dagger1MvpViewStateActivity, Dagger1MvpViewStateFragment

    public interface Injector
    Injector will be passed around in the application to get access to the dagger.ObjectGraph.

    Since Injector can be Activity or Fragment, never ever store the injector since it can cause memory leaks. If there is really no other solution then pass around the object graph getObjectGraph()

    Since:
    1.0.0
